The paper focuses on investigating the ability of deep learning algorithms to infer visual concepts, specifically using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of machine intelligence and learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The experiments involve training and testing the algorithms, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses language understanding and semantics, which could potentially place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
